The Keiser Report  No. 227
= Max Keiser and Stacy Herbert =
Saturday, 24 December 2011


[sebaygo1]


This time Max and Stacy look back on 2011 from GIABO to Tango Down, the fight against bankster occupation has been setting the global agenda. From the banking scandal headlines, they look at Greek woes, suckling bankers and Blythe Masters' immaculately conceived Credit Default Swap. 

They also discuss the circle of Hell that former prosecutor, William K. Black suggests is just punishment for Septic Tank Scum banksters and the bizarre view that President Obama has from 40,000 feet.
